All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary Error Summary 
    Class Description
    AmbiguousMemberException
    Exception class for if a field or method cannot be distinguished when defined multiple times
    Argument
    Utility class designed to determine which ArgumentNode child is required.
    ArgumentNode
    Abstract class for nodes that represent an argument such as a primitive constant, String or variable
    CallMethodNode
    Rule node that deals with calling source methods.
    CompilationFailureException
    Exception for when compilation of source, test or generated test Java files has failed
    CompilationLogger
    CompilationLogger stores the errors that have resulted from the compilation of Java files./ All errors are written to a log file located within a default directory
    ConstantNode
    Rule node that deals with constants of any primitive type, (such as int, char, boolean etc)
    ExpectationNode
    Rule node that deals with creating expectation objects.
    ExpectationObject<T>
    ExpectationObject stores the first value to be compared as an instance field of a generic type.
    Expectations
    Class designed to create the appropriate ExpectationObject and record the result
    FieldNode
    Rule node that deals explicitly with static or instance fields from source classes.
    FileFinder
    Static class providing methods capable of collecting Java files as well as finding files from a specific directory and getting the class name from a provided file.
    GetValueNode
    Rule node that deals with getting the value of fields, variables or method calls.
    ImportCollector  
    InvalidRuleStructureException
    Exception to be thrown when a rule has an invalid structure.
    JavaClassAnalyzer
    Class that stores instances of SourceClass for the source classes that have been loaded into the classpath.
    JavaClassCompiler
    Provides methods with different types and combinations of parameters for compiling classes.
    JavaClassLoader
    JavaClassLoader extends the built-in ClassLoader class.
    MethodArgumentNode
    Rule node that deals with the arguments for method calls.
    MethodNode
    Rule node that deals with calling a method.
    Parser
    Parses the rules extracted from test classes to generate the code required to create test suites.
    RuleExtractor
    Class that extracts rules from the required files and passes the rules to the Runner class.
    Runner
    Runner acts as the main controller of the testing framework.
    SourceClass
    Utility class to store details of a source class and provide methods of analysis
    SourceClassLoader
    Utility class designed to load specifically source classes
    SourceField
    Class which represents a field from a compiled and loaded source class
    SourceMember
    Superclass for the source fields and methods from which SourceField and SourceMethod classes inherit
    SourceMethod
    Class which represents a method from a compiled and loaded source class
    StoreValueNode
    Rule node that deals with storing the value of fields, variables or method calls in a specified variable.
    StringNode
    Rule node that deals with Strings as arguments
    TestCaseGenerator
    Generates the code for a single test case based on the tree generated during rule validation
    TestClass
    Utility class to store details of a test class and provide methods of analysis
    TestClassAnalyzer
    Class that stores instances of TestClass for the test classes that have been loaded into the classpath.
    TestClassLoader
    Utility class designed to load specifically test classes
    TestExecutor
    TestExecutor is designed to execute all the tests from all the generated test suites and record the outcomes of each test.
    TestField
    Utility class used to represent a field defined by a class and provide methods capable of reading the represented field's value
    TestLogger
    TestLogger records the results of all test suites and their associated test cases in a log file located within a default directory.
    TestMember
    Utility superclass used to represent a member defined by a class
    TestMethod
    Utility class used to represent a method defined by a class and provide methods capable of calling and reading the represented method's return value
    TestSuiteGenerator  
    TreeNode
    Interface for the expected implementation of nodes to be added to a tree in order to validate rules and generate the required code.
    TypeIdentifier
    Class designed to determine type name
    UnidentifiedCallException
    Exception to be thrown when a specific class's member cannot be found
    UnparsableRuleException
    Exception to be thrown when a rule cannot be parsed
    UnsatisfiedExpectationError
    Exception to be thrown when an expectation has not been satisfied
    ValueNode
    Rule node that deals with getting values from methods, fields, variables and arguments.
    Variable
    Utility class for storing and managing details of a variable declared within the test case generation.
    VariableNode
    Rule node that deals with constants of any primitive type, (such as int, char, boolean etc)
    VariableStore
    Utility class designed to store all the variables that exist when the current test suite is being created.
